title: US Chips Act Mandates Contenders To Share Excess Profits With Country, Refrain From Buybacks And China
description: The U.S. today launched the first CHIPS for America funding opportunity for manufacturing incentives to restore U.S. leadership in semiconductor manufacturing, support good-paying jobs across the semiconductor supply chain, and advance U.S. economic and national security. It will require recipients of more than $150 million in direct funding to share a portion of any cash flows or returns that exceed the applicant’s projections above an established threshold with the U.S. government. title: Applied Materials Launches Sculpta To Cut Advanced Chipmaking Cost, Wins Intel As Client
description: Applied Materials, Inc (NASDAQ: AMAT) showcased a patterning technology that helped chipmakers to create high-performance transistors and interconnect wiring with fewer EUV lithography steps, thereby lowering the cost, complexity, and environmental impact of advanced chipmaking.
